WEBVTT

00:06.528 --> 00:06.745
.

00:06.789 --> 00:09.052
- Previously, on "Happy!"...

00:10.314 --> 00:11.228
- [laughs] You can see me!
- What the hell?

00:12.360 --> 00:13.100
- I ain't your
imaginary friend.

00:14.144 --> 00:14.188
I don't even
want to think about

00:15.015 --> 00:15.363
what that would look like.

00:16.320 --> 00:18.192
I'm Hailey's imaginary friend.

00:18.235 --> 00:20.716
- Got you!
- It's really you.

00:20.759 --> 00:23.240
Sonny Shine.
[screams]

00:23.284 --> 00:25.460
- Where is she?
- You should stop by my town.

00:25.503 --> 00:27.375
I can't speak to her
frame of mind.

00:27.418 --> 00:30.117
- This is evil.
They can't get away with this.

00:30.160 --> 00:32.380
- They can, but not forever.

00:32.423 --> 00:35.731
- If Mikey gave Orcus to Blue,
all is lost.

00:35.774 --> 00:37.863
- Yes, yes, that's why
we must stop him.

00:37.907 --> 00:39.343
- [exhales]

00:39.387 --> 00:40.823
[screaming and grunting]

00:40.866 --> 00:43.260
[bones snapping]

00:44.348 --> 00:45.784
- [grunts]

00:47.438 --> 00:49.223
I'm hungry.

00:49.266 --> 00:51.747
- Why do you have to go?
- You're growing up.

00:51.790 --> 00:56.317
You'll forget all about
that silly horse.

00:56.360 --> 00:57.883
See, the thing
about imaginary friends

00:57.927 --> 00:59.624
is we're kind of supposed to

00:59.668 --> 01:01.931
help out the person
who needs us the most.

01:01.974 --> 01:03.759
Here it comes.
[hooves clattering]

01:03.802 --> 01:06.588
- Yeah, it is.
- Here comes the fun!

01:06.631 --> 01:08.155
- Oh, boy, here it goes.
- Are you ready?

01:08.198 --> 01:09.591
- [retches]

01:10.809 --> 01:12.289
[dramatic music]

01:12.333 --> 01:14.161
- Please, please help.

01:14.204 --> 01:16.685
Dear God.
Oh, Jesus Christ.

01:16.728 --> 01:20.471
[indistinct prayers]

01:20.515 --> 01:27.522
♪

01:31.178 --> 01:33.702
- I place myself in the
word of your God.

01:33.745 --> 01:36.313
[sobs, mutters]

01:38.272 --> 01:41.449
- Don't be afraid.

01:41.492 --> 01:45.279
Heaven waits for us.

01:45.322 --> 01:46.976
We'll all die together.

01:47.019 --> 01:54.157
♪

01:56.246 --> 01:59.293
[indistinct prayers continue]

02:21.315 --> 02:22.968
[upbeat music]

02:23.012 --> 02:25.971
[women singing
in foreign language]

02:26.015 --> 02:33.196
♪

02:33.544 --> 02:36.591
[indistinct chatter]

02:38.593 --> 02:41.509
- [screams]

02:41.552 --> 02:44.512
[crowd screaming in panic]

03:02.921 --> 03:05.924
[dramatic music]

03:05.968 --> 03:10.712
♪

03:10.755 --> 03:13.758
[women shouting]

03:26.423 --> 03:28.425
- [yells]

03:32.429 --> 03:35.650
[both yelling]

03:35.693 --> 03:39.001
[heavy breathing]

03:39.044 --> 03:46.051
♪

04:08.683 --> 04:11.729
[device beeping]

04:12.817 --> 04:16.081
[beeping intensifies]

04:16.125 --> 04:17.648
[gasps]

04:17.692 --> 04:18.997
- [screams]

04:19.041 --> 04:20.999
[explosion]

04:21.043 --> 04:25.003
[timer beeping]

04:25.047 --> 04:27.745
[explosion]

04:27.789 --> 04:29.094
- [grunts]

04:29.138 --> 04:32.315
[explosions]

04:35.623 --> 04:38.669
[distant explosions]

04:39.801 --> 04:41.150
[beeping intensifies]

04:41.193 --> 04:44.153
[upbeat foreign music]

04:44.196 --> 04:51.160
♪

04:51.203 --> 04:53.989
- [wails]

04:54.032 --> 04:56.165
[bell dings]

04:56.208 --> 04:59.386
- [snoring]

05:14.488 --> 05:17.491
[soft music]

05:17.534 --> 05:22.670
♪

05:22.713 --> 05:24.889
- ♪ 7:00 AM,
waking up in the morning ♪

05:24.933 --> 05:26.848
both: ♪ Got to be fresh,
got to go downstairs ♪

05:26.891 --> 05:28.763
♪ Got to have my bowl,
got to have cereal ♪

05:28.806 --> 05:29.981
- [grunts]

05:30.025 --> 05:31.026
- ♪ The time is going

05:31.069 --> 05:32.462
- [hisses]

05:32.506 --> 05:34.725
- Top of the morning
to you, partner!

05:34.769 --> 05:36.814
- Oh, fuck off.

05:36.858 --> 05:38.425
- We're getting
our act together, Nick.

05:38.468 --> 05:41.036
No more drinking,
no more illegal narcotics.

05:41.079 --> 05:44.082
No more whoring.
- Right.

05:44.126 --> 05:46.041
[blow dryer whirs]

05:46.084 --> 05:47.521
And most of all,

05:47.564 --> 05:49.914
no more filling chumps
full of hot lead.

05:49.958 --> 05:52.656
- ♪ It's Friday, Friday

05:52.700 --> 05:54.832
♪ Got to get down on Friday

05:54.876 --> 05:58.923
♪ Everybody's looking forward
to the weekend, weekend ♪

05:58.967 --> 06:03.058
♪ Friday, Friday,
getting down on Friday ♪

06:03.101 --> 06:07.062
- Boy, Nick,
your breath sure is fresh.

06:07.105 --> 06:09.543
I don't miss
the old us at all, Nick.

06:09.586 --> 06:11.066
You're doing super,

06:11.109 --> 06:13.764
and Hailey's going to be
so proud of you.

06:13.808 --> 06:15.766
- ♪ Looking forward
to the weekend ♪

06:15.810 --> 06:18.769
[tires screech,
car horn honking]

06:18.813 --> 06:20.902
- I'm walking here!
- Move!

06:20.945 --> 06:22.730
- I'm walking here!
- Get out of the way!

06:22.773 --> 06:24.601
- ♪ It's Friday, Friday

06:24.645 --> 06:25.994
- Hey, up yours, buddy!

06:26.037 --> 06:27.952
- ♪ We so excited

06:27.996 --> 06:32.479
- I'm Deandra, and I'm, um...

06:32.522 --> 06:34.568
uh...

06:34.611 --> 06:36.961
uh, I'm a--I'm--

06:37.005 --> 06:39.616
I'm...
[coffee dribbling]

06:39.660 --> 06:41.226
[chair creaks]

06:41.270 --> 06:44.491
- [lips smacking]

06:44.534 --> 06:46.188
Let 'er rip, sis!

06:46.231 --> 06:48.277
You're only as sick
as your secrets.

06:48.320 --> 06:51.541
That's what I always say.
- Uh...

06:51.585 --> 06:53.282
- Nick, bear claw!

06:53.325 --> 06:55.632
- [laughs]

06:55.676 --> 06:57.678
- Are you even signed up?

06:57.721 --> 06:59.810
- He's just here
for the coffee.

07:01.638 --> 07:03.205
- This place
is depressing, Nick.

07:03.248 --> 07:05.033
I'm so glad you've
evolved into such a total

07:05.076 --> 07:07.296
Zen wizard master
of your darker impulses.

07:07.339 --> 07:11.082
- Evolved, huh?
You're goddamn right.

07:11.126 --> 07:12.693
Evolved.

07:12.736 --> 07:13.998
[ominous music]

07:14.042 --> 07:16.087
[groans]

07:16.131 --> 07:19.308
[heavy breathing]

07:19.351 --> 07:21.005
So thirsty.

07:21.049 --> 07:23.965
[monkey screeching]
I'm thirsty.

07:24.008 --> 07:26.924
[monkey screeching intensifies]
So, so thirsty.

07:26.968 --> 07:29.753
- Now, Nick, you promised.

07:29.797 --> 07:31.842
♪

07:32.843 --> 07:34.758
You've been coming down
with a cold

07:34.802 --> 07:36.151
for two months, Nick.

07:36.194 --> 07:37.979
- It's why I need
the good stuff, Hap.

07:38.022 --> 07:40.808
- What you need
is a big glass of OJ,

07:40.851 --> 07:44.072
a bowl of chicken soup,
and a nice, warm blanket.

07:44.115 --> 07:45.856
- OJ did it.

07:45.900 --> 07:49.643
Don't you read the news?

07:49.686 --> 07:52.210
Okay, we're good.

07:52.254 --> 07:54.691
[dog barking]

07:54.735 --> 07:58.260
- Bike lane, moron!
[bike bell dings]

07:58.303 --> 08:01.263
[bright orchestral music]

08:01.306 --> 08:03.221
♪

08:03.265 --> 08:04.832
[lasers whoosh]

08:04.875 --> 08:08.139
[screams]

08:08.183 --> 08:11.142
[chainsaw revs]

08:11.186 --> 08:18.193
♪

08:22.893 --> 08:25.853
[bike bell dings]
- Dickhead!

08:25.896 --> 08:28.682
- Your imagination is a pretty
F'd up place to live, Nick.

08:28.725 --> 08:30.640
You know that, right?
- [grunts]

08:30.684 --> 08:31.989
Oh!

08:32.033 --> 08:33.643
[clock ticks]

08:33.687 --> 08:35.210
Hallelujah,
my little blue asshole.

08:35.253 --> 08:37.212
Guess what time it is?

08:37.255 --> 08:39.214
[school bell rings]

08:39.257 --> 08:42.217
[groovy music]

08:42.260 --> 08:46.874
♪

08:46.917 --> 08:48.919
Meat tenderizer.
- What?

08:48.963 --> 08:51.400
- Powdered form right there in
the herbs and spices section.

08:51.443 --> 08:53.358
Gets the blood right out
of cotton underwear.

08:53.402 --> 08:55.317
- You're kidding on me, Nicki!
- I stand before you shitless.

08:55.360 --> 08:57.188
- Seasoned or unseasoned?

08:57.232 --> 08:58.799
- Depends on how spicy
you like it down there.

08:58.842 --> 09:01.236
[laughter]

09:01.279 --> 09:02.846
- What's wrong with your kid?

09:02.890 --> 09:04.674
- What's wrong with your face?

09:04.718 --> 09:06.894
[laughter]

09:06.937 --> 09:09.897
[gentle music]

09:09.940 --> 09:13.074
♪

09:13.117 --> 09:14.945
- All right, till next time.
Be well, be safe.

09:14.989 --> 09:17.252
And remember to lock down
them stroller wheels, huh?

09:19.646 --> 09:21.778
Hey, kiddo.

09:21.822 --> 09:24.128
Um, 3:00.
You ready to--

09:24.172 --> 09:26.130
- The teacher wants
to talk to you.

09:27.958 --> 09:29.786
- What did I do?

09:31.701 --> 09:33.921
Ms. Palm.
- Please, have a seat.

09:33.964 --> 09:35.313
[chair clatters]

09:35.357 --> 09:37.098
- I've heard so much about you.

09:37.141 --> 09:38.926
But if I'd known
we were meeting,

09:38.969 --> 09:40.449
I'd have brought an apple.

09:40.492 --> 09:42.320
- Well, I'll get
right to the point.

09:42.364 --> 09:44.148
- Good.
- We all understand that

09:44.192 --> 09:47.674
Hailey has been through
a very traumatic experience.

09:47.717 --> 09:49.937
- Well, I took care of that...
[laughs]

09:49.980 --> 09:52.287
[pops lips]
[both grunt]

09:52.330 --> 09:53.984
- You're doing the thing.

09:54.028 --> 09:56.683
- Uh, surely,
as a former police officer,

09:56.726 --> 09:58.989
you understand
it's not that simple.

09:59.033 --> 10:02.732
The last two months have seen
a series of incidents--

10:02.776 --> 10:04.473
school property broken,

10:04.516 --> 10:07.868
a campaign of psychological
harassment against the staff--

10:07.911 --> 10:09.347
- Psychological harassment?

10:09.391 --> 10:10.871
- Hailey would never do
anything like that!

10:10.914 --> 10:12.263
- Shut your nozzle.

10:14.135 --> 10:15.876
I know, you know,
my daughter, I mean,

10:15.919 --> 10:17.486
she would never
do nothing like that.

10:17.529 --> 10:19.488
- You know,
I've met Ms. Hansen.

10:19.531 --> 10:22.012
- Well?
- I can't imagine where Hailey

10:22.056 --> 10:25.494
could have acquired this
anti-authoritarian attitude.

10:25.537 --> 10:28.497
- Maybe the problem here is
that she's not being offered...

10:28.540 --> 10:31.369
[stammers]
A proper creative outlet.

10:31.413 --> 10:34.242
- A creative outlet?
- Hey, take me for example.

10:34.285 --> 10:36.026
I had my issues at school.

10:36.070 --> 10:39.073
And if it hadn't been for
extracurricular activities...

10:39.116 --> 10:41.902
[furious guitar solo]

10:41.945 --> 10:43.251
Whoo!

10:43.294 --> 10:45.340
Who knows how
I would have wound up?

10:45.383 --> 10:48.169
- I understand you've had a
change of employment recently.

10:48.212 --> 10:49.953
- What's that have to do with
the price of ass in Pittsburgh?

10:49.997 --> 10:51.999
- Dad.
- Instability in the home

10:52.042 --> 10:53.435
can lead to changes
in a child's behavior.

10:53.478 --> 10:55.263
- Instability?
What are you talking about?

10:55.306 --> 10:57.178
I drive a cab. There's nothing
more stable than that.

10:57.221 --> 10:59.354
That's a good job, right?
- Wow.

10:59.397 --> 11:02.531
I haven't taken
an actual cab in years.

11:02.574 --> 11:04.925
I mean, do you mean Uber?
- Yeah.

11:04.968 --> 11:06.187
What?
What's Uber?

11:06.230 --> 11:07.841
- Oh, God.
- Who asked you?

11:07.884 --> 11:09.538
It's an app!
I knew that.

11:09.581 --> 11:13.150
I am not going to sit here
and tolerate someone

11:13.194 --> 11:16.023
casting aspersions
on my daughter.

11:16.066 --> 11:18.765
I don't suppose
you have any evidence

11:18.808 --> 11:20.854
to back up these wild claims?

11:20.897 --> 11:23.421
- Would you, uh, care to review

11:23.465 --> 11:25.859
the security camera
tapes with me?

11:27.338 --> 11:29.340
They're HD.

11:29.384 --> 11:31.168
[dramatic music]

11:31.212 --> 11:33.127
- I know your kind.
- Dad, no.

11:33.170 --> 11:34.868
- I've been fighting you
my whole life.

11:34.911 --> 11:38.001
With your Birkenstocks,
avocado toast,

11:38.045 --> 11:39.916
five college degrees
that ain't worth

11:39.960 --> 11:42.919
the "paper du toilette"
that they're printed on.

11:42.963 --> 11:45.226
Looking down your nose
at us poor slobs

11:45.269 --> 11:47.097
like Queen Shit
on Dick Mountain.

11:47.141 --> 11:49.099
Well, let me
tell you something.

11:49.143 --> 11:50.797
If that's the way
it's going to be around here,

11:50.840 --> 11:52.146
then screw this school,

11:52.189 --> 11:53.800
because she's better off
someplace else.

11:53.843 --> 11:55.584
And do you know what
the real crime is here?

11:55.627 --> 11:59.240
Do you know what makes me want
to fall to my knees and weep?

11:59.283 --> 12:00.981
You let down your hair, you put
on a little bit of lipstick,

12:01.024 --> 12:02.330
you wouldn't be half bad.

12:02.373 --> 12:04.071
- Nick!
Sensitivity.

12:04.114 --> 12:06.464
- This meeting was intended
as a wake-up call,

12:06.508 --> 12:10.904
but taking into account
her situation,

12:10.947 --> 12:13.428
perhaps Hailey needs
more attention and help

12:13.471 --> 12:15.169
than we're equipped to provide.

12:15.212 --> 12:16.866
- What kind of
frame job is this?

12:16.910 --> 12:18.433
- Dad, I did it.

12:18.476 --> 12:20.348
I did it.
I broke the windows.

12:20.391 --> 12:22.916
I did the
psychological harassment.

12:22.959 --> 12:24.526
It was me.

12:24.569 --> 12:28.095
[soft music]

12:28.138 --> 12:29.313
- [scoffs]

12:29.357 --> 12:31.272
Every kid's got problems.

12:31.315 --> 12:34.971
- And we need to learn to solve
those problems constructively,

12:35.015 --> 12:37.539
using sensible,
adult techniques

12:37.582 --> 12:41.369
like discussion, negotiation,

12:41.412 --> 12:43.414
compromise.

12:45.242 --> 12:47.375
- Compromise?

12:47.418 --> 12:50.378
[Gregorian chanting]

12:50.421 --> 12:55.470
♪

12:55.513 --> 12:57.428
- Let's face it.

12:57.472 --> 12:59.430
Easter sucks.

12:59.474 --> 13:01.650
[upbeat dance music]

13:01.693 --> 13:05.567
Dude, you got the IP,
don't get me wrong.

13:05.610 --> 13:09.397
Jesus H. Christ,
resurrected from the dead.

13:09.440 --> 13:13.618
I--it don't get
sexier than that.

13:13.662 --> 13:17.144
But what have you done with it?
Colored eggs?

13:17.187 --> 13:19.233
The Easter bunny?

13:19.276 --> 13:22.540
I mean, I like marshmallow
Peeps as much as the next guy.

13:22.584 --> 13:25.152
I--I ate a whole bag
on the flight out.

13:25.195 --> 13:26.457
But come on!

13:26.501 --> 13:29.417
Easter, it's the
Alzheimer's-ravaged

13:29.460 --> 13:31.636
mother-in-law of holidays.

13:31.680 --> 13:36.032
Tolerated, not celebrated.

13:37.599 --> 13:39.470
That's why I'm here.

13:40.950 --> 13:44.345
I'm sure you're familiar
with my work,

13:44.388 --> 13:46.303
my legacy.

13:46.347 --> 13:49.437
My status as
beloved global icon

13:49.480 --> 13:51.613
to children of all ages.

13:51.656 --> 13:55.530
What I'm offering you today
is a chance to be a part

13:55.573 --> 13:59.360
of the biggest holiday
re-branding of all time.

13:59.403 --> 14:02.711
I'm talking four quadrants.

14:02.754 --> 14:05.235
I'm talking mass marketing.

14:05.279 --> 14:07.281
Walmart wars.

14:07.324 --> 14:09.979
Easter presents,
Easter carols.

14:10.023 --> 14:11.720
Chocolate Wishies
instead of those

14:11.763 --> 14:14.070
horny Pagan fertility bunnies.

14:14.114 --> 14:18.335
A multi-trillion dollar
holiday bonanza

14:18.379 --> 14:20.990
to rival Christmas itself!

14:21.034 --> 14:22.209
[shutter clicks]

14:22.252 --> 14:26.561
Nuns exploding on 5th Avenue.

14:26.604 --> 14:29.303
Tragic, yes,

14:29.346 --> 14:33.568
but this can work
to our advantage.

14:33.611 --> 14:35.570
Everyone's talking about Easter

14:35.613 --> 14:37.485
for the first time since

14:37.528 --> 14:40.053
Mel Gibson struck
box office gold

14:40.096 --> 14:42.011
telling your story.

14:42.055 --> 14:45.232
The war on Easter is real,

14:45.275 --> 14:47.582
and we can win it!

14:47.625 --> 14:50.019
[inspirational music]

14:50.063 --> 14:52.065
We're going to

14:52.108 --> 14:56.547
Make Easter Great Again

14:56.591 --> 14:58.680
for the first time.

14:58.723 --> 15:01.422
Now...

15:01.465 --> 15:03.641
I can do it with
or without you.

15:03.685 --> 15:05.252
And it's the 20-teens.

15:05.295 --> 15:07.776
The holiday's ain't just
for believers anymore.

15:07.819 --> 15:10.648
♪

15:10.692 --> 15:12.476
But I'm here,

15:12.520 --> 15:16.654
at your feet.

15:16.698 --> 15:23.705
♪

15:25.750 --> 15:28.797
I want you on board,
big fella.

15:28.840 --> 15:32.235
I want your brand
front and center

15:32.279 --> 15:34.629
for the big rollout,

15:34.672 --> 15:38.198
starting quarterback
for Team Sonny.

15:40.113 --> 15:42.506
What do you say, Pope Daddy?

15:46.467 --> 15:49.209
- I like it.

15:49.252 --> 15:52.125
- [laughs]

15:55.171 --> 15:55.606
.

15:55.650 --> 15:58.174
[rousing music]

15:58.653 --> 16:00.916
♪

16:00.960 --> 16:03.179
[bird caws]

16:03.223 --> 16:10.447
♪

16:13.973 --> 16:15.975
- No, no.

16:18.760 --> 16:20.240
Tired.

16:20.283 --> 16:23.460
[indistinct distant chatter]

16:25.854 --> 16:28.770
[soft orchestral music]

16:28.813 --> 16:30.772
- Wow.

16:30.815 --> 16:34.776
Just, wow.

16:34.819 --> 16:37.779
[liquid trickling]

16:37.822 --> 16:40.825
Little Blues.

16:40.869 --> 16:44.699
You were amazing last night.

16:44.742 --> 16:47.136
[tense music]

16:47.180 --> 16:50.183
[buzzer blaring]

16:50.226 --> 16:53.186
[indistinct announcement
over PA]

16:53.229 --> 17:00.236
♪

17:21.083 --> 17:23.738
- Look, it's Blue rat,

17:23.781 --> 17:25.261
like in movie.

17:25.305 --> 17:28.656
[imitates mouse biting]

17:28.699 --> 17:33.008
You know you are
a dead man, Blue rat.

17:33.052 --> 17:35.880
I just hope it's me who gets--
[grunts]

17:35.924 --> 17:37.230
- [screams]

17:37.273 --> 17:40.755
I ain't no rat,
you Bolshevik asshole!

17:40.798 --> 17:43.018
Get off!
[grunts]

17:43.062 --> 17:44.933
[rattling]

17:44.976 --> 17:48.676
What is that?
What is--what is that?

17:48.719 --> 17:50.199
[grunts]

17:50.243 --> 17:52.288
[tense music]

17:52.332 --> 17:54.595
[grunting]

17:54.638 --> 17:56.336
[men chuckling]

17:56.379 --> 18:02.342
♪

18:02.385 --> 18:05.345
- A present from the Bug.

18:05.388 --> 18:06.955
[bright rock music]

18:06.998 --> 18:10.611
- ♪ Sonny

18:10.654 --> 18:13.875
♪ Ooh, Sonny Shine

18:13.918 --> 18:16.617
[music distorts]

18:16.660 --> 18:19.707
♪

18:19.750 --> 18:23.014
- Amanda, are you all right?

18:23.058 --> 18:25.104
- I'm sorry, Doctor, I'm fine.
- [chuckles]

18:25.147 --> 18:31.153
♪

18:31.197 --> 18:35.201
- It's just--is there
something else we can put on?

18:35.244 --> 18:37.246
- Why?
Kids love Sonny.

18:37.290 --> 18:39.857
Hey, right?
Huh, huh, see?

18:39.901 --> 18:43.687
♪ Sonny, Sonny, Sonny,
rock and roll ♪

18:43.731 --> 18:45.733
♪ Rock and roll

18:45.776 --> 18:48.170
[tense music]

18:48.214 --> 18:49.954
[drill whirring]

18:49.998 --> 18:53.262
[heavy dance music]

18:53.306 --> 18:56.004
♪ Rock and roll
- I'm sorry.

18:56.047 --> 18:58.789
- Okay, I got this.

19:01.357 --> 19:04.099
- Well, here she is,
safe and sound.

19:04.143 --> 19:05.753
- What happened?

19:05.796 --> 19:07.929
- I told you she was good,
Nick.

19:07.972 --> 19:09.322
- You know how
you're always saying

19:09.365 --> 19:10.975
we got a one-in-a-million kid,

19:11.019 --> 19:12.760
and you're not getting
any argument from me.

19:12.803 --> 19:15.284
Kid's got a personality
like she's a superstar,

19:15.328 --> 19:19.114
brightest star in the sky,
and sometimes,

19:19.158 --> 19:21.334
the other stars, you know,
who ain't so bright,

19:21.377 --> 19:22.900
they may feel
a little intimidated.

19:22.944 --> 19:25.207
- Ms. Palm wanted to talk
to you or dad.

19:25.251 --> 19:27.122
She got Dad.
- Oh.

19:27.166 --> 19:30.430
- Our little Hailey got
singled out for behavior

19:30.473 --> 19:33.041
that any other kid
with a backbone would have--

19:33.084 --> 19:34.825
this Ms. Palm character.

19:34.869 --> 19:37.132
I mean, she presents us with
all these trumped-up charges,

19:37.176 --> 19:39.961
totally unsubstantiated,
and I step forward, like,

19:40.004 --> 19:42.268
you know, any good father
would, naturally.

19:42.311 --> 19:43.791
I mean, if you're looking
for someone to blame--

19:43.834 --> 19:46.881
- I don't have to look
very far.

19:46.924 --> 19:48.709
- No, no.
Tell her, tell her.

19:48.752 --> 19:50.450
- Dad got me
kicked out of school.

19:50.493 --> 19:53.844
- She set off the fire alarms.

19:53.888 --> 19:56.456
- Wait for me over there.

19:56.499 --> 19:59.154
- Snitches get stitches.

19:59.198 --> 20:02.070
- You, outside.

20:02.113 --> 20:04.028
- I haven't seen Amanda
this disappointed since

20:04.072 --> 20:06.074
you let me out of the
pillowcase last New Year's,

20:06.117 --> 20:07.815
and your giggle pole was--

20:07.858 --> 20:09.991
- What happened on New Year's
stays on New...

20:10.034 --> 20:12.863
[car honking]

20:12.907 --> 20:15.083
- All right.

20:15.126 --> 20:16.780
- All right?

20:16.824 --> 20:18.304
- This child's been through
a nightmare, Nick.

20:18.347 --> 20:20.262
We all have.

20:20.306 --> 20:22.264
We're kidding ourselves if we
think it hasn't affected her.

20:22.308 --> 20:23.483
- Man, she's
a tough little hombre.

20:23.526 --> 20:25.833
- She's a child, Nick.

20:25.876 --> 20:29.184
And she's seen things
no child should have to see.

20:29.228 --> 20:33.493
Maybe this is exactly
what she needs.

20:33.536 --> 20:36.452
You've noticed this place
runs 40,000 a year?

20:36.496 --> 20:39.150
[soft music]

20:39.194 --> 20:42.066
- Boy, we must have spent
a gajillion hours in here

20:42.110 --> 20:44.330
playing with all the toys,
the games,

20:44.373 --> 20:47.376
the waiting for Amanda
to get done with the work.

20:47.420 --> 20:49.465
[Nick and Amanda arguing
behind the window]

20:49.509 --> 20:53.295
But I guess we're all
grown out of that stuff,

20:53.339 --> 20:55.993
aren't we?

20:56.037 --> 20:57.473
- You know,
I thought about trying

20:57.517 --> 20:59.910
the whole nun thing once--
the vows, the habit.

20:59.954 --> 21:02.130
- I thought you were Jewish.
- Well, that's the thing.

21:02.173 --> 21:04.263
- I'd like to see you
stick to a vow of celibacy.

21:04.306 --> 21:06.352
[meows]

21:06.395 --> 21:09.224
- [barking]
- [hisses]

21:09.268 --> 21:11.052
- [barks]

21:11.095 --> 21:13.141
- So you said you were drugged,
and when you woke up,

21:13.184 --> 21:15.883
you were fitted with the
latest in ISIS fashion.

21:15.926 --> 21:18.451
- Witnesses say you and your
sisters were running around

21:18.494 --> 21:22.542
like headless chickens
looking for something.

21:22.585 --> 21:26.981
- He told us there was
a device hidden in an egg.

21:27.024 --> 21:29.113
- So you're saying
this was an Easter egg hunt?

21:29.157 --> 21:31.246
- Mm, never was a fan.
- See, Christmas,

21:31.290 --> 21:32.552
they put the presents
where you can find them.

21:32.595 --> 21:34.118
- See, that's what
I'm talking about.

21:34.162 --> 21:35.903
- Yes,

21:35.946 --> 21:38.471
an Easter egg hunt.

21:38.514 --> 21:41.300
He said--he said--

21:41.343 --> 21:43.563
- Come on, spit it out.

21:43.606 --> 21:46.130
- The device would detonate
the vest closest to it,

21:46.174 --> 21:47.828
and the others would be safe.

21:47.871 --> 21:49.873
- Oh, I see.

21:49.917 --> 21:51.092
So you thought you were

21:51.135 --> 21:53.312
sacrificing yourself
for the others.

21:53.355 --> 21:55.270
- Got us a
Good Samaritan, Hubble.

21:55.314 --> 21:56.880
- Ought to canonize this one.

21:56.924 --> 21:59.579
- Funny thing is,
the opposite happened.

21:59.622 --> 22:02.277
- You were saved,
and the others--

22:02.321 --> 22:05.280
- Boosh!

22:05.324 --> 22:06.934
- Guess it was your lucky day.

22:06.977 --> 22:09.937
- No, I wanted to die.
- No one said you didn't.

22:09.980 --> 22:11.417
- Ease off, Julie Andrews.

22:11.460 --> 22:14.420
- We'll never know,
on account of everyone else

22:14.463 --> 22:16.596
who was there was just
power-washed off the streets

22:16.639 --> 22:18.293
by a sanitation crew.

22:18.337 --> 22:20.556
- Well, now,

22:20.600 --> 22:24.952
that's not entirely true.

22:24.995 --> 22:27.955
[tense music]

22:27.998 --> 22:29.086
♪

22:29.130 --> 22:31.132
- No.

22:31.175 --> 22:32.438
No, don't make me
talk about him.

22:32.481 --> 22:34.091
- Come on, don't be shy.

22:34.135 --> 22:36.050
- He just blew up all
your little sister sisters.

22:36.093 --> 22:38.922
- You want us to catch this
son of a gun, don't you?

22:38.966 --> 22:42.622
♪

22:42.665 --> 22:45.973
- He said--he said--

22:46.016 --> 22:47.409
[chairs creak softly]

22:47.453 --> 22:49.629
- Who said?

22:49.672 --> 22:51.413
- [sobs]

22:51.457 --> 22:53.372
The Bunny.

22:53.415 --> 22:55.374
[ominous music]

22:57.376 --> 23:00.640
Black like licorice,

23:00.683 --> 23:05.209
and terrible,
big, biting teeth...

23:05.253 --> 23:07.473
[shudders]

23:07.516 --> 23:11.390
Big, floppy ears,

23:11.433 --> 23:14.044
and the eye--

23:14.088 --> 23:16.656
the pink bunny eye...

23:16.699 --> 23:18.484
[dramatic musical flourish]

23:18.527 --> 23:20.921
[bunny munching]

23:20.964 --> 23:24.011
- The kids will wait here
until you sound the horn.

23:24.054 --> 23:25.360
Then, the curtain drops,

23:25.404 --> 23:27.144
and they run out
to the Easter meadow.

23:27.188 --> 23:28.668
- I cannot believe
"Good Morning America"

23:28.711 --> 23:31.192
is blue-balling us.
I'm Scooter frickin' Sterling.

23:31.235 --> 23:34.674
- Junior, they know.
They still might come through.

23:34.717 --> 23:36.589
The Times article
had an impact,

23:36.632 --> 23:38.460
but I think you can still
expect a very successful event.

23:38.504 --> 23:40.462
- Oh, that hack job?
Are you kidding me?

23:40.506 --> 23:42.638
We raised over $8 million
for inner-city kids last year.

23:42.682 --> 23:44.379
They can't expect every penny
to actually go to the,

23:44.423 --> 23:45.554
you know--
- The kids.

23:45.598 --> 23:47.077
- Yeah.
- Right.

23:47.121 --> 23:48.339
The foundation
does have expenses.

23:48.383 --> 23:49.993
- Damn right, it does.

23:50.037 --> 23:52.996
[groovy music]

23:53.040 --> 23:55.346
♪

23:55.390 --> 23:57.000
- Well, they did
get to keep the candy.

23:57.044 --> 23:58.393
- Look, I got to go
take care of something.

23:58.437 --> 23:59.612
You can hold down
the fort, right?

23:59.655 --> 24:02.005
- Yep.
- Okay.

24:02.049 --> 24:05.226
♪

24:05.269 --> 24:06.706
Yeah.

24:06.749 --> 24:10.013
You are Scooter
fucking Sterling, baby.

24:10.057 --> 24:13.974
You're about to get your D S'd.

24:14.017 --> 24:17.412
Oh, yeah.
Very sexy lighting.

24:17.456 --> 24:19.153
I like the mood in here.

24:19.196 --> 24:22.156
It's getting the blood flow
down to my dee-ock.

24:22.199 --> 24:23.505
Oh, hi.

24:23.549 --> 24:25.028
[foreboding music]

24:25.072 --> 24:28.379
You look fantastic.

24:28.423 --> 24:30.425
What the hell's
the matter with you?

24:30.469 --> 24:33.036
Okay, you're freaked out,
I get it.

24:33.080 --> 24:35.038
Good news, that's my thing.

24:35.082 --> 24:36.518
This is, like, a game thing
we're going to play.

24:36.562 --> 24:38.302
Okay, a little trauma play.

24:38.346 --> 24:40.000
You're scared.
I'm strong.

24:40.043 --> 24:41.610
A couple of ground rules
for me off the bat--

24:41.654 --> 24:43.743
one, I like a lot of teeth
down there.

24:43.786 --> 24:46.049
Two, my safe word
is "Tallahassee."

24:46.093 --> 24:48.051
[grunting]

24:48.095 --> 24:51.054
[dramatic music]

24:51.098 --> 24:52.447
♪

24:55.624 --> 24:55.842
.

24:55.885 --> 24:58.671
- So, here we are.

25:01.500 --> 25:02.718
- It's so light and bright.

25:02.762 --> 25:04.546
- Right?

25:04.590 --> 25:06.853
- It's time to settle down
in a real family home.

25:06.896 --> 25:10.770
- Oh, this place has "family"
all over it...[chuckles]

25:10.813 --> 25:12.685
Speaking of which,
state law requires me

25:12.728 --> 25:14.513
to disclose certain things
about the property

25:14.556 --> 25:15.862
before we continue.

25:15.905 --> 25:17.559
A few months before listing,

25:17.603 --> 25:20.736
this property was the site
of a triple homicide.

25:21.998 --> 25:23.957
Young couple, about your age,

25:24.000 --> 25:25.872
and their mother-in-law
visiting from Boston.

25:25.915 --> 25:28.048
The intruder--
- Intruder?

25:28.091 --> 25:30.746
- Was on PCP, tripping balls,
dick, all of it.

25:30.790 --> 25:32.574
He butchered them like cattle.

25:32.618 --> 25:34.489
They were found in this
open concept kitchen,

25:34.533 --> 25:37.187
which I'm sure you'll agree,
is super cute.

25:37.231 --> 25:39.233
- It is nice.

25:39.276 --> 25:41.888
- Built-in coffee maker?

25:43.629 --> 25:45.500
- A lot of folks
might not want a property

25:45.544 --> 25:47.154
with this type of history.

25:47.197 --> 25:49.722
But on the upside,
statistically speaking,

25:49.765 --> 25:52.202
the odds of something like that
ever happening again

25:52.246 --> 25:55.902
in the exact same location?

25:55.945 --> 25:57.730
Close to zero.

25:57.773 --> 25:59.775
- Well, it is a real bargain
for this neighborhood.

25:59.819 --> 26:01.168
- And between you and me,

26:01.211 --> 26:02.909
I think the seller
will move a little.

26:02.952 --> 26:05.085
- And like she says, a place
that's been broken into once,

26:05.128 --> 26:06.608
it's not likely that--

26:06.652 --> 26:08.218
[toilet flushes]
- Oh!

26:08.262 --> 26:10.960
- The self-flushing toilets.

26:11.004 --> 26:13.572
I--I'm gonna get that
taken care of.

26:13.615 --> 26:15.269
[tense music]

26:15.312 --> 26:17.271
You guys love the place.

26:17.314 --> 26:20.187
We'll talk, yeah?
I'll call you.

26:20.230 --> 26:21.841
- Self-flushing?
- Yeah.

26:21.884 --> 26:24.060
- Wow.
- It's amazing technology.

26:24.104 --> 26:29.022
♪

26:29.065 --> 26:31.067
- Jesus Christ, Nick!

26:33.679 --> 26:35.550
[Happy squeaks]

26:38.640 --> 26:40.642
- A little privacy here, huh?
- What are you doing here?

26:40.686 --> 26:41.948
- All right,
you need to calm down.

26:41.991 --> 26:45.952
- Oh, oh!
I can never un-see it!

26:45.995 --> 26:49.956
- "Calm down," Nick?
This is my job.

26:49.999 --> 26:53.133
Are you stalking me?
- Oh, great, her again.

26:53.176 --> 26:55.048
- What?
No.

26:55.091 --> 26:56.658
I wouldn't call it that.

26:56.702 --> 26:58.138
I was at the bus shelter,
I looked down.

26:58.181 --> 26:59.922
Who do I see?
Mary McCarthy, realtor.

26:59.966 --> 27:01.881
I must have been sitting
on your face for ten minutes.

27:01.924 --> 27:03.665
- All right, that's it.
Out of this house.

27:03.709 --> 27:06.886
It was you--the squatter
in the condo on north 6th.

27:06.929 --> 27:08.670
I should have
recognized that smell.

27:08.714 --> 27:10.150
- That was a nice place.

27:10.193 --> 27:13.240
A little transitional
for my tastes, but very nice.

27:13.283 --> 27:15.111
- Oh, Jesus!
- Oh, it's not, like,

27:15.155 --> 27:16.330
something you
haven't seen before.

27:16.373 --> 27:18.593
- Don't remind me.

27:18.637 --> 27:21.291
Please promise me
you will destroy this thing

27:21.335 --> 27:23.337
by fire before
contamination spreads.

27:23.380 --> 27:25.165
- Oh, there it is.

27:25.208 --> 27:27.776
- Damn it, Sax.
This is not okay.

27:27.820 --> 27:30.692
- Hey, you can't
screw this up for me.

27:30.736 --> 27:32.825
I got Hailey
a couple days a month.

27:32.868 --> 27:36.176
Man, I just need a place where
she can sleep in a nice bed

27:36.219 --> 27:38.134
that's clean.

27:38.178 --> 27:39.832
You know, someplace normal.

27:39.875 --> 27:42.312
How's a guy like me supposed
to afford a place like that?

27:42.356 --> 27:43.966
- Your problem was
never making money.

27:44.010 --> 27:45.751
It was drinking it
and snorting it.

27:45.794 --> 27:48.667
- Yeah, well, you're
looking at the new Nick Sax.

27:48.710 --> 27:50.016
I'm clean.

27:52.366 --> 27:55.282
Ish.
Six weeks.

27:55.325 --> 27:57.719
[exhales]

27:57.763 --> 27:59.199
- Sax.
- Yeah.

27:59.242 --> 28:01.375
- Not so high and mighty now,
are we?

28:01.418 --> 28:04.900
- I just want her
to be proud of me, Mar.

28:04.944 --> 28:07.337
I'm getting back on my feet.

28:07.381 --> 28:09.992
I'll clean up before I go.

28:10.036 --> 28:12.255
- Do you ever think about
what happened?

28:14.040 --> 28:16.956
- Oh, that.

28:16.999 --> 28:19.262
[soft music]

28:19.306 --> 28:22.048
Why would I?
We won.

28:22.091 --> 28:23.919
- Did we?
- Well, you know.

28:23.963 --> 28:25.878
Hailey's had her ups and downs,
but she's all right,

28:25.921 --> 28:27.227
and she's way more
than I deserve.

28:27.270 --> 28:30.709
So yeah, we did.

28:30.752 --> 28:32.754
- You ever think about
going after Sonny Shine?

28:32.798 --> 28:35.061
- Nick, you don't seriously
believe that Sonny Shine

28:35.104 --> 28:37.803
had anything to do with--

28:37.846 --> 28:39.718
- Moved on, Mar.

28:39.761 --> 28:41.850
The way I look at it, the world
is full of cockroaches.

28:41.894 --> 28:43.243
That's more the rule
than the exception.

28:43.286 --> 28:44.984
- [blows raspberry]
- So you squash one.

28:45.027 --> 28:47.116
What the hell
does that get you?

28:47.160 --> 28:50.424
Thousands more just like them
behind every wall,

28:50.467 --> 28:51.991
even these.

28:52.034 --> 28:54.428
- This really is a new you.
- Yeah.

28:54.471 --> 28:55.951
How about you?

28:55.995 --> 28:58.911
- Oh, well,
you can see I've moved on.

28:58.954 --> 29:00.260
- Yeah.

29:00.303 --> 29:03.089
I find that outfit, um...

29:03.132 --> 29:04.786
hot, strangely.

29:04.830 --> 29:06.092
I don't know. I don't know.
- [laughs softly]

29:06.135 --> 29:07.789
- You know what
I don't understand, though?

29:07.833 --> 29:09.791
Why didn't you put up more
of a fight for your badge?

29:09.835 --> 29:11.445
- There's no fight when
the fix is in, Sax.

29:11.488 --> 29:13.795
You know that.
Blue had half the department

29:13.839 --> 29:15.101
on the take when he went down.

29:15.144 --> 29:16.885
Somehow, IA concludes

29:16.929 --> 29:19.105
I'm the only rotten banana
of the bunch?

29:19.148 --> 29:21.890
- One way to look at it.

29:21.934 --> 29:23.805
"You had it coming" is another.

29:23.849 --> 29:25.198
- [inhales]

29:25.241 --> 29:28.723
So that's it, huh?
Keep our heads down.

29:28.767 --> 29:30.377
Take it day by day.

29:30.420 --> 29:32.945
Hope trouble doesn't
come looking for us.

29:32.988 --> 29:35.208
- Sure.

29:35.251 --> 29:37.819
It seems like neither one of us
was cut out to be a cop.

29:39.255 --> 29:41.823
Your cookies suck.

29:41.867 --> 29:43.303
- You got shit on your face.

29:43.346 --> 29:45.174
- Sonny's not a cockroach.

29:45.218 --> 29:47.829
I don't believe it,
and neither does Hailey.

29:47.873 --> 29:50.136
♪ He's the man
in the rainbow castle ♪

29:50.179 --> 29:52.312
♪ A friend to you and--

29:52.355 --> 29:55.184
huh?

29:55.228 --> 29:56.838
Nick!

29:56.882 --> 29:59.145
- Yeah, what is it?

29:59.188 --> 30:02.888
- Uh, nothing.

30:02.931 --> 30:05.891
[indistinct chatter]

30:05.934 --> 30:08.894
[tense music]

30:08.937 --> 30:11.897
[baby crying]

30:11.940 --> 30:16.510
♪

30:16.553 --> 30:18.991
- [exhales]

30:19.034 --> 30:22.037
Blue, it's great to see you...

30:24.300 --> 30:26.215
In here, I mean.

30:26.259 --> 30:28.827
- An angel of grace and light,
as usual.

30:28.870 --> 30:31.046
- Cut the shit, brother.
I'm here to tell you something.

30:31.090 --> 30:32.526
- [groans]

30:32.569 --> 30:34.528
- I'm here to tell you about
the nightmares

30:34.571 --> 30:36.922
you've been having.

30:36.965 --> 30:39.185
- I sleep like
a little pink baby.

30:39.228 --> 30:40.839
- About the blackouts,

30:40.882 --> 30:42.971
about the things that
you can't remember.

30:43.015 --> 30:44.320
- [growls]

30:44.364 --> 30:45.887
- Well,
there's a perfect reason--

30:45.931 --> 30:48.194
[inhales sharply]
[soft clicking]

30:48.237 --> 30:49.543
What's that sound?

30:49.586 --> 30:51.980
- Nothing in the world
is going to bring back

30:52.024 --> 30:54.809
my sweet Mikey, but believe me,

30:54.853 --> 30:56.332
I'm going to take
a lifetime's worth

30:56.376 --> 30:59.118
of satisfaction in knowing
that the last great thing

30:59.161 --> 31:02.034
he did on this earth
was to screw you over.

31:02.077 --> 31:04.253
- Mikey?

31:04.297 --> 31:07.213
No.

31:07.256 --> 31:09.128
Mikey gave me a password.

31:09.171 --> 31:11.870
- There was no password,
you moron.

31:11.913 --> 31:14.960
Mikey carried
an ancient spirits,

31:15.003 --> 31:16.918
an evil thing,

31:16.962 --> 31:19.921
passed from
the old dawn to you,

31:19.965 --> 31:22.402
like a virus, like AIDS.

31:22.445 --> 31:24.883
- I know--
I know what a virus is, Isa--

31:24.926 --> 31:26.319
[soft clicking continues]

31:26.362 --> 31:30.105
[scoffs]

31:30.149 --> 31:32.368
Do you hear that sound?

31:32.412 --> 31:35.545
- There's something
living in your mind, Blue.

31:35.589 --> 31:37.504
You can feel it, can't you?

31:37.547 --> 31:40.942
Scratching in the dark,
trying to get out.

31:40.986 --> 31:43.249
♪

31:45.468 --> 31:48.950
- [British accent]
Isabella, Isabella.

31:48.994 --> 31:52.258
It's a name of Hebrew origin.

31:52.301 --> 31:54.521
Did you know?

31:54.564 --> 31:58.438
It means "devoted to God."

32:00.005 --> 32:01.920
Beautiful name.

32:01.963 --> 32:05.010
Devout.

32:05.053 --> 32:08.100
- Why are you
talking like Madonna?

32:08.143 --> 32:11.103
- Come closer.

32:11.146 --> 32:13.627
I need to tell you a secret.

32:13.670 --> 32:16.325
Something about Mikey,

32:16.369 --> 32:19.328
something even his mother
didn't know.

32:19.372 --> 32:22.331
[soft whimsical music]

32:22.375 --> 32:27.119
♪

32:27.162 --> 32:30.165
And who is this vision?

32:30.209 --> 32:33.038
- You don't know who I am,

32:33.081 --> 32:35.649
but I know who you are.

32:35.692 --> 32:39.435
Orcus, god of death.

32:39.479 --> 32:43.135
You've been passing down
for ages,

32:43.178 --> 32:46.181
from Scaramucci to Scaramucci.

32:55.538 --> 32:59.020
- How many times have you
passed from body to body?

32:59.064 --> 33:03.198
- More than I can count
with all my fingers,

33:03.242 --> 33:04.983
with all my toes.

33:05.026 --> 33:07.115
- But this time,
it was different.

33:07.159 --> 33:08.987
The transfer was corrupted.

33:09.030 --> 33:11.598
- It is like
you unplug your device

33:11.641 --> 33:15.036
before the update is complete.

33:15.080 --> 33:16.995
- Two lousy souls

33:17.038 --> 33:20.955
sharing one pasty, white body.

33:20.999 --> 33:25.046
- And you will be living
in that prison,

33:25.090 --> 33:27.701
in that body, forever.

33:27.744 --> 33:32.532
- Bella,
Orcus lives in our bloodline.

33:32.575 --> 33:35.622
We don't need Blue.

33:35.665 --> 33:37.058
[dramatic musical sting]

33:37.102 --> 33:39.669
Let me enter you.

33:39.713 --> 33:42.150
Let me come inside you.

33:42.194 --> 33:44.631
- Um--
- Let me leave this

33:44.674 --> 33:48.156
graceless, flaccid
sack of flesh behind.

33:48.200 --> 33:52.378
Together, you and I will rule.

33:52.421 --> 33:55.120
- That will never happen.

33:55.163 --> 33:59.124
- Don't be so sure, harridan.

33:59.167 --> 34:01.996
- She's the last
of the Scaramucci.

34:06.435 --> 34:09.003
- Yeah, so suck it.
Wait, what?

34:09.047 --> 34:11.092
- [screams]

34:11.136 --> 34:14.095
[dramatic music]

34:14.139 --> 34:17.664
♪

34:17.707 --> 34:21.015
- Never be free!
[laughs]

34:21.059 --> 34:22.712
Never be free!

34:22.756 --> 34:24.236
- [screams]

34:24.279 --> 34:27.065
- [speaking Italian]
- [grunting]

34:27.108 --> 34:30.111
♪

34:30.155 --> 34:32.592
- [laughs]
[indistinct radio chatter]

34:32.635 --> 34:35.290
You will never be free...
[laughs]

34:35.334 --> 34:36.683
Never!

34:39.773 --> 34:39.990
.

34:40.034 --> 34:41.775
- 40K a year--

34:42.950 --> 34:45.039
them sisters ought to be
wearing masks.

34:45.083 --> 34:46.780
What the hell is wrong
with public school, anyway?

34:46.823 --> 34:49.043
Plenty of good Americans
went to public school, right?

34:49.087 --> 34:50.914
Lincoln.

34:50.958 --> 34:52.742
Einstein.
- Oprah.

34:52.786 --> 34:55.136
- I'm supposed to make that
kind of money driving a cab.

34:55.180 --> 34:57.704
[babbles mockingly]

34:57.747 --> 35:00.489
Uber!
[car horn blares]

35:00.533 --> 35:03.710
Taking out the trash,
that's what I'm good at.

35:03.753 --> 35:06.060
And by "trash," I mean people
who need to get whacked.

35:06.104 --> 35:08.845
- You promised.
No whacking.

35:08.889 --> 35:10.717
- How the hell is anyone
supposed to keep their head

35:10.760 --> 35:14.199
above water in this stinking
town without killing people?

35:14.242 --> 35:17.724
- Um, right here is good.

35:17.767 --> 35:19.508
- I thought you said uptown.

35:19.552 --> 35:21.858
- Did I?

35:31.129 --> 35:33.653
- There you go, buddy.
Get that paper.

35:33.696 --> 35:35.916
You see that?
Get that money.

35:35.959 --> 35:38.571
[woman screams]

35:38.614 --> 35:41.182
- I don't know, Hap.

35:41.226 --> 35:44.881
Maybe California
ain't looking so bad.

35:44.925 --> 35:47.928
- Nick,
can I ask you something?

35:47.971 --> 35:49.669
Something kind of personal--
- Who's this asshole?

35:49.712 --> 35:52.237
- Shit, shit, shit.

35:52.280 --> 35:54.804
- Yeah, well,
the world's full of it, pal.

35:54.848 --> 35:57.851
So you got a particular
destination in mind, or what?

35:59.592 --> 36:02.116
- Listen, you look like
a "can-do" kind of guy.

36:02.160 --> 36:03.596
- Hear that all the time.

36:03.639 --> 36:07.034
- I need a girl for a party.

36:07.077 --> 36:08.818
My own date just ran off on me,

36:08.862 --> 36:10.255
and I don't want to look like
an asshole showing up alone.

36:10.298 --> 36:11.821
- Yeah, well, you know,
I got to tell you,

36:11.865 --> 36:13.171
that ain't really
my line of work.

36:13.214 --> 36:15.129
- It's just a party, man.
- Look, pal.

36:15.173 --> 36:17.566
I realize I may not give off
the rosiest first impression,

36:17.610 --> 36:19.133
but I'm not quite sure
where you'd arrive

36:19.177 --> 36:20.830
at the rather
presumptuous notion--

36:20.874 --> 36:24.225
- I'll give you 1,000 bucks
if you find me a girl.

36:24.269 --> 36:25.792
Hm?

36:25.835 --> 36:28.795
[groovy music]

36:28.838 --> 36:35.845
♪

36:45.290 --> 36:47.161
You're a life-saver, bro.

36:47.205 --> 36:50.164
- I am.
I really am.

36:50.208 --> 36:52.645
- So, um, I'm assuming there's

36:52.688 --> 36:54.299
going to be other girls
at this party?

36:54.342 --> 36:55.822
- Yeah, of course, baby.

36:55.865 --> 36:57.867
[laughs]

36:57.911 --> 37:01.175
You don't mind me asking,
what's your blood type?

37:01.219 --> 37:08.226
♪

37:13.796 --> 37:15.842
Yeah, this is it.

37:18.061 --> 37:21.674
- Wow, Sax.
I really owe you for this one.

37:21.717 --> 37:24.198
- Excuse me for trying
to throw a friend a bone.

37:24.242 --> 37:26.156
- You're friends?
- All right, all right, look.

37:26.200 --> 37:27.680
You heard the guy.
It's a party.

37:27.723 --> 37:29.334
A little conversation,
a little dancing.

37:29.377 --> 37:33.294
- Oh, God, can't I just blow
everyone and be done with it?

37:33.338 --> 37:36.079
- Really?

37:36.123 --> 37:38.212
Is romance really that dead?

37:38.256 --> 37:41.650
Now, I'm not saying
there's anything, um,

37:41.694 --> 37:43.826
untoward about this situation,

37:43.870 --> 37:45.872
but should anything arise that

37:45.915 --> 37:48.048
involves certain acts--
of an adult nature, I mean--

37:48.091 --> 37:49.354
I think we should negotiate
some consideration.

37:49.397 --> 37:50.920
- Uh, why are you
talking like that?

37:50.964 --> 37:52.270
- 20%.
- 10.

37:52.313 --> 37:55.795
- 15.
- Did you bring a calculator?

37:55.838 --> 37:58.276
- All right, 10.

38:05.021 --> 38:08.198
- This is her.
Well, yeah.

38:16.859 --> 38:19.688
- Seems legit.

38:19.732 --> 38:22.256
What, no music?

38:22.300 --> 38:24.345
There you go.

38:24.389 --> 38:26.869
[Jermaine Stewart's "We Don't
Have To Take Our Clothes Off"]

38:26.913 --> 38:28.393
- You changing into this.

38:28.436 --> 38:30.873
- Ah, costumes.
That's fun.

38:30.917 --> 38:33.093
- ♪ We could dance and party

38:33.136 --> 38:34.964
♪ All night
- ♪ All night

38:35.008 --> 38:37.184
- ♪ And drink
some cherry wine ♪

38:37.227 --> 38:38.707
♪ Uh-huh

38:38.751 --> 38:40.100
- Maybe I ought to
just stick around,

38:40.143 --> 38:41.406
make sure everything's okay.
- You know what?

38:41.449 --> 38:44.104
Just wait for me outside.

38:44.147 --> 38:46.019
- What the fuck you looking at?

38:46.062 --> 38:47.890
- Sax, would you please

38:47.934 --> 38:49.979
just get the hell out of here
and let me do my job?

38:50.023 --> 38:52.895
You're making everything weird.

38:52.939 --> 38:55.376
- ♪ Na, na

38:55.420 --> 38:56.943
♪ Just slow down

38:56.986 --> 38:58.423
- I'm making it weird?

38:58.466 --> 39:00.381
- ♪ A man wants
to be approached ♪

39:00.425 --> 39:02.165
♪ Cool and romantically

39:02.209 --> 39:03.689
- "I'm" making it weird.

39:03.732 --> 39:05.430
- ♪ I've got needs

39:05.473 --> 39:06.996
[soft music]

39:07.040 --> 39:09.825
- Why do things
have to change, Nick?

39:09.869 --> 39:13.133
- Oh, the big questions, huh?

39:13.176 --> 39:16.919
What brought that on?

39:16.963 --> 39:18.312
- [sniffs]

39:18.356 --> 39:20.270
- Look, Hap,

39:20.314 --> 39:23.012
you can't fight it.

39:23.056 --> 39:25.101
The rain gutters are
stuffed with poor suckers

39:25.145 --> 39:27.800
who thought they could
hang on to the way it was.

39:29.889 --> 39:32.065
Change is inevitable.

39:32.108 --> 39:35.111
- Then why haven't you changed
that shirt in three weeks?

39:37.984 --> 39:39.986
- Hap, you want to make
yourself useful?

39:40.029 --> 39:41.857
- [gasps] Of course I do.

39:41.901 --> 39:44.120
- Fly your tiny little
blue ass up into that party,

39:44.164 --> 39:45.470
take a look around,
tell me if there's anything

39:45.513 --> 39:48.386
funny going on.
- Like, funny "ha-ha?"

39:49.865 --> 39:51.998
- No, the other kind.

39:52.041 --> 39:53.434
[upbeat music]

39:53.478 --> 39:55.958
- Guys,

39:56.002 --> 39:57.482
even for me, this is fucked up.

39:57.525 --> 40:04.750
♪

40:11.887 --> 40:14.063
[glasses tinkering]

40:16.065 --> 40:18.024
- Nick!
- Sweet Jesus.

40:18.067 --> 40:20.766
- That's the silliest kind
of party I ever saw, Nick.

40:20.809 --> 40:23.856
There's a big bathtub full
of ice but no sodas in it,

40:23.899 --> 40:27.381
and a yellow guy in the back
hooked up to a giant juice box.

40:27.425 --> 40:29.514
- What do you mean "yellow?"
Like, Chinese?

40:29.557 --> 40:31.820
- Nick, that's offensive.

40:31.864 --> 40:34.823
I mean yellow,
like a pineapple popsicle.

40:34.867 --> 40:36.999
[foreboding music]

40:37.043 --> 40:38.523
- [grunting]

40:38.566 --> 40:40.481
- Wait, wait!

40:40.525 --> 40:42.265
And up!
[claps hands]

40:42.309 --> 40:44.180
Spill on aisle three.

40:44.224 --> 40:46.879
Look, I'm as open-minded
as anyone--

40:46.922 --> 40:48.837
more so, as a point of fact--

40:48.881 --> 40:50.186
but I think we can all agree.

40:50.230 --> 40:51.840
This is no one's idea
of a party.

40:51.884 --> 40:54.974
- Yo, taxi driver,
get the fuck out of here.

40:55.017 --> 40:58.151
- You talking to me?

40:58.194 --> 41:00.370
Anyway, look, let's not get
carried away, all right?

41:00.414 --> 41:04.113
I think that we find ourselves
in a bit of a pickle, you know?

41:04.157 --> 41:08.509
But I know that we can, um...

41:08.553 --> 41:10.903
find a way to solve
our problems,

41:10.946 --> 41:14.515
you know, constructively,
using, um,

41:14.559 --> 41:19.085
sensible,
adult techniques such as...

41:19.128 --> 41:21.087
Discussion!

41:21.130 --> 41:23.959
Negotiation and compromise.

41:24.003 --> 41:25.308
[dramatic music]

41:25.352 --> 41:26.832
[grunting]

41:26.875 --> 41:29.008
[blood splatters]

41:29.051 --> 41:31.358
Um...
- [gags]

41:32.968 --> 41:35.318
[ax clatters]

41:35.362 --> 41:39.061
- That wasn't my fault.
You're going to be fine.

41:39.105 --> 41:40.410
- [grunting]

41:40.454 --> 41:42.978
- Yeah, you're good.

41:43.022 --> 41:45.111
You know, more accidents
happen in the workplace.

41:45.154 --> 41:46.591
- [groans loudly]
- You're gonna be fine.

41:46.634 --> 41:49.028
- [yelling]
- Uh...

41:49.071 --> 41:50.856
Oh, boy.
- [gags]

41:50.899 --> 41:53.206
I mean--all right, look,

41:53.249 --> 41:55.034
but he--he came at me...

41:55.077 --> 41:57.471
[mutters]

41:57.515 --> 42:00.039
I mean that as a compliment.

42:00.082 --> 42:01.867
- Nick!
- Ah--whoa!

42:01.910 --> 42:04.870
[rock music]

42:04.913 --> 42:11.920
♪

42:30.678 --> 42:32.245
[bones crunching]

42:32.288 --> 42:33.899
Ah, cheeseburgers.

42:33.942 --> 42:35.465
- [grunts]

42:40.427 --> 42:43.517
- Son of a bitch.
You're a heavy bastard.

42:43.561 --> 42:45.867
[grunting]

42:49.088 --> 42:51.438
It's nothing personal, pal.
This is just for your own good.

42:51.481 --> 42:53.309
Consider it like time out.

42:53.353 --> 42:54.528
Hey, fedora.

42:54.572 --> 42:56.356
Look, your guys
are going to get hurt.

42:56.399 --> 42:58.140
Let's just everyone...
[inhales, exhales]

42:58.184 --> 42:59.925
Right?
- [groans]

42:59.968 --> 43:01.666
[truck whirrs]
- Well, I hope that

43:01.709 --> 43:03.668
you have learned a very
valuable lesson tonight.

43:03.711 --> 43:05.539
I know I have.

43:05.583 --> 43:07.672
When we deal with our problems

43:07.715 --> 43:10.022
out of a place of anger,

43:10.065 --> 43:11.501
bad things happen.

43:11.545 --> 43:14.635
But when we confront them
with kindness...

43:14.679 --> 43:17.638
[mellow music]

43:17.682 --> 43:20.641
♪

43:20.685 --> 43:22.382
Fuck it!

43:22.425 --> 43:24.602
- But Nick, you promised
you wouldn't kill anyone--

43:24.645 --> 43:26.386
- No guns.
- You killed everyone!

43:26.429 --> 43:27.692
There's corpses.
How would you--

43:27.735 --> 43:29.215
- What happened?
- Nick, why?

43:29.258 --> 43:32.305
- Eh...
- Entrails, bones.

43:32.348 --> 43:34.002
Blood--just, all blood!

43:34.046 --> 43:36.048
- Is that a liver?
- How can--

43:36.091 --> 43:38.006
- I think it's more
of a spleen.

43:38.050 --> 43:40.705
- [stammering, howls]

43:40.748 --> 43:43.664
- You, what's something
like that worth?

43:43.708 --> 43:47.102
- $500, maybe.

43:47.146 --> 43:48.451
- How about a kidney?

43:48.495 --> 43:51.367
- In good condition?

43:51.411 --> 43:53.674
Over 100,000, easy.

43:53.718 --> 43:55.502
- Holy giblets,
I'm standing in the middle

43:55.545 --> 43:59.245
of a goddamn gold mine
of blood and guts.

43:59.288 --> 44:01.595
[flesh squelches]

44:01.639 --> 44:04.642
Now, what would you say
qualifies as good condition?

44:05.773 --> 44:07.732
[siren wails faintly]

44:07.775 --> 44:09.559
- [gasps sharply]

44:09.603 --> 44:11.387
[heavy breathing]

44:11.431 --> 44:13.128
[gasps]

44:15.653 --> 44:18.394
- Bad dream, baby?

44:18.438 --> 44:20.396
- I don't remember.

44:20.440 --> 44:23.704
- You don't have
anything to be afraid of.

44:23.748 --> 44:26.620
All the bad people
who tried to hurt you

44:26.664 --> 44:29.318
are either gone,
or locked up somewhere

44:29.362 --> 44:32.757
where they can never
get out again.

44:32.800 --> 44:35.368
- All of them?

44:35.411 --> 44:36.761
- All of them.

44:36.804 --> 44:39.764
[synth music]

44:39.807 --> 44:46.988
♪

45:06.704 --> 45:08.227
- [sighs]

45:18.759 --> 45:25.766
♪

45:35.689 --> 45:38.736
[blob gurgling, popping]

45:40.389 --> 45:43.349
[soft acoustic music]

45:43.392 --> 45:50.399
♪

45:56.449 --> 45:58.712
- ♪ A strange kind of love

45:58.756 --> 46:00.148
[door creaks]

46:00.192 --> 46:02.281
♪ A strange kind of feeling

46:02.324 --> 46:04.544
- [muffled sobs]

46:04.587 --> 46:07.677
- ♪ Swims through your eyes

46:07.721 --> 46:11.551
♪

46:11.594 --> 46:14.162
♪ And like the doors

46:14.206 --> 46:17.731
♪ To a wide, vast dominion

46:17.775 --> 46:19.777
- What do you
have in mind for him?

46:21.779 --> 46:23.693
No, no, don't tell me.

46:23.737 --> 46:26.740
I--I love surprises.

46:26.784 --> 46:29.177
- How did you get in here?

46:29.221 --> 46:30.744
- When you're as
rich and famous as I am,

46:30.788 --> 46:33.834
let's just say it pays to keep
tabs on your employees--

46:33.878 --> 46:38.143
even a gold star
go-getter like you,

46:38.186 --> 46:42.234
left to their own...

46:42.277 --> 46:44.236
devices,
the next thing you know,

46:44.279 --> 46:46.760
the stenographer is downloading

46:46.804 --> 46:49.807
granny porn on company time.

46:49.850 --> 46:53.767
- Please put that down.

46:53.811 --> 46:55.813
- I'll let you
get back to work.

46:59.817 --> 47:01.906
That lady cop,

47:01.949 --> 47:03.908
you know, the one that put
Blue Scaramucci in jail--

47:03.951 --> 47:05.474
whatever happened to her?

47:05.518 --> 47:06.867
- You had her
thrown off the force.

47:06.911 --> 47:08.608
Ruined her life, remember?

47:08.651 --> 47:10.915
- Did I?
Huh.

47:10.958 --> 47:13.395
Oh, and the other one.

47:13.439 --> 47:14.919
The big--the big,
smelly one.

47:14.962 --> 47:16.921
Nick Tuba, right?
- Sax.

47:16.964 --> 47:19.488
- Sax, that's it.
What happened to him?

47:19.532 --> 47:21.534
- How would I know?

47:23.797 --> 47:27.888
- Ah, well, we have
bigger fish to fry, don't we,

47:27.932 --> 47:30.195
my floppy-eared friend.

47:30.238 --> 47:33.285
[chuckles]

47:33.328 --> 47:36.288
But maybe I should have
just killed him anyway.

47:36.331 --> 47:38.333
You know, revenge.

47:38.377 --> 47:40.466
I mean, everybody
loves revenge, right?

47:40.509 --> 47:42.207
Even you.

47:42.250 --> 47:45.863
- I am a professional,
Mr. Shine.

47:45.906 --> 47:50.650
My focus is my work,
and only my work.

47:50.693 --> 47:53.653
[tense synth music]

47:53.696 --> 47:56.656
♪

47:56.699 --> 47:59.398
I don't have
a vengeful bone in my body.

47:59.441 --> 48:06.448
♪
